reviews.name: Danillo A.
reviews.review: THEY STEAL YOUR MONEY! The price is $10 for the first hour, and they ask you to pay it before you go to your car. I stayed 30 minutes, paid $10, and went to my car. I was not feeling super well, so I decided to eat my lunch before driving. I left the garage at minute 52, less than the 1 hour I paid. They requested another payment because I OVERSTAYED 15 minutes after the payment! I paid for 1 hour, stayed 52 minutes, and was forced to pay for 2 hours. When I told them I did not want to pay twice for the same hour, the guy left me there, with my car locked by the exit, and told me I would not leave without paying. He did not even want to talk and disappeared. Only after I called the police and threatened to block the exit, more than 30 minutes later, a supervisor came to talk to me. He said that I passed my "grace period" after my payment. This does not make ANY sense. A person can stay 1 hour plus 15 minutes for a grace period for $10. However, I stayed 52 minutes and needed to pay twice just because I followed the signs and paid before entering my car instead of paying by the gate. If I had just paid at the same time by the gate, it would be 10 dollars. But because I followed the sign and paid a few minutes earlier, I had to pay twice. This is ridiculous. The guy was disrespectful, and the entire situation was outrageous! Just because I was too tired and the police said they would take a long time to come, I paid another $10 to go home. Now I want my money back and someone t

reviews.name: Jeanette R.
reviews.review:
We tried this place when we found out that our hotel was charging $75.00 a day!!  we were able to park our car for a total of 3 days and it was less then 1 day at the hotel.
We will definitely use ParkMe again!!

reviews.name: Jonathan D.
reviews.review: Wanted less expensive option for morning meeting at S.F.Public. It's about 8 blocks from the library-- I don't mind walking through the Tenderloin. Did see 2 cops running & 4 cop cars (wrong way through one-way traffic) take off in pursuit of a cell phone thief. Staff was polite and efficient. Cell phone check in with reservation was easy. They had my car at the front of the lot's 1st floor at the time I said I'd return. There's a little Burmese restaurant 2 blocks away on Eddy. Had nice hot bowl of catfish chowder before picking up the car.

reviews.name: Maya Y.
reviews.review: So glad we did this. Whenever we drive up to SF, we always end up wandering around and finding either sketchy or overpriced parking. This helped make pur day much less stressful and worrisome. The attendants were friendly and helpful, and happily took us up to the 2nd story when we wanted to drop off some stuff. Thank you!

reviews.name: Edward S.
reviews.review: Worked great. I'd suggest adding a map view when the list of search results comes up to make choosing a space a little easier. Will definitely use your service again.

reviews.name: Heather J.
reviews.review:
This was my first time using ParkMe, as I was driving up to San Francisco
for an all-day meeting and wanted to find reasonably-priced parking within
a couple blocks of the conference hotel. I didn't know reservations were a
new feature, but it was super helpful to be able to plan ahead and not
scramble for parking at 7:30AM. The website helped me find several garages
that were significantly better priced than the conference hotel. All I had
to do was show my reservation at the garage, and the attendants took care
of the rest.

reviews.name: Heather J.
reviews.review: I needed a parking spot for an all-day meeting at the Hilton Union Square, and I had no interest in paying $50+ to park in the hotel garage. Rock Star Parking was just a block or two away, easy to find, and the pre-booked price was great. The garage is in the Tenderloin, so the surroundings are a bit sketchy, but the attendants were professional and the garage felt totally secure. Would recommend.

reviews.name: C B.
reviews.review:
I would leave a negative review if I could. I stayed at the Parc 55 and had my car parked by valet. Upon returning my car, I had a ding in the passenger side door. I reported this immediately to an attendant. I later received a letter from Connecticut stating the ding was pre- existing (which is a highly incorrect statement). I asked for evidence to support this claim. The representative from Propark then emailed me a piece of paper from Propark with a car diagram on it with an X on the passenger side door. The representative stated this was the proof that the ding was pre- existing. Unbelievable! This was not a diagram filled out after a joint inspection by the attendant and myself in which I signed in agreement. This was offered after the fact. When I made the initial complaint at Parc 55, the supervisor took a report and did not even mention this "evidence". This evidence was created after the report was taken I am sure. Before I leave my car with any valet service, I walk around it in order to check the body. I take very good care of my car. Due to the valet service,
My family and I will never stay at this location again. Where is the honorable and just business practice? This whole experience was highly unsavory and dishonest.

Luckily we had a dash cam and found where they ran into the wall and presented the information to the manager Tovik. youtu.be/i7Dkj-myY5E . reviews.review: I attended a party at the Marine's Memorial Club on a Friday night.  I appreciated the speed and recovery of my car and GREAT service. I was greeted at 6:00 by friendly staff who took excellent care of my car. When I returned at 10:30 P.M. I was verbally harassed and pestered by a "street person" who follwed me into the waiting area as I presented my blue claim check. I ignored and made zero eye contact with this Caucasian 40-year-old who persisted on having a conversation with me. The 490 Post Street Garage valet proceeded quickly to retrieve my car and help me to the safety of my locked car. The "street person commented, "What a nice ride." By this time approximately 5 minutes, the street person exited, and the valet ran out of the driveway to usher me out to safety. I am so sad about the state of affairs in our downtown area of San Francisco. I am a 5th generation native and thank you for helping me last night.

reviews.review: I parked a rental vehicle at this location in Dec 2020 under the impression it was a 24hr parking garage. It is advertised online as being 24hr and the large signage outside the garage also state it is 24hr. At 2:30am, when I went to retrieve my vehicle in order to return it to the airport and catch a flight, the garage was closed with no staff around. The multiple contact numbers online did not work and ACE parking claimed it should've been open. I spoke to the neighbouring hotel and they claimed the garage had been operating 24hrs since at least march. This resulted in me missing my flight and having to pay a fee to change to a later flight. This is a cowboy operation, do not park at this location.

All in all it was a good experience--very convenient to reserve ahead of time so that we didn't have to go looking for a garage and potentially be late for our event. Thanks so much.

Horrible experience. After paying at the pay station and immediately walking to my car, we drove down from the fourth floor to the exit on the first. Due to traffic congestion inside the garage, we exceeded the time permitted. 

Once denied exit, I used the intercom to ask for assistance. I was only given short responses which were difficult to understand due to the poor audio quality but were instructing me to leave my car to walk to the pay station. After several requests for clarification, they stopped answering my calls via the intercom entirely.  Eventually, an employee tasked with traffic management refused to help with exiting, but he did direct traffic to let me back up so I could park on the bottom floor and make the payment. After parking on the first floor, and heading toward the pay station, one employee did listen to my complaint and offered to let me out through a different exit.

Two of the three employees I had to deal with were extremely unprofessional and frankly quite rude. The entire experience was extremely frustrating.

reviews.name: Chelsea P.
reviews.review: Literally the worst people ever. I had a cargo van with me to unload a bed and bed frame. Keep in mind I LIVE at THE PARAMOUNT. My rent is paying for their salary. I was parked for no more than 10 minutes bringing things up to my apartment and coming down. The man demands my keys and told me he will go park if it it disturbs anyone. I said I will be leaving once I finish bringing the bed upstairs and he said okay but to still give him the keys. I come back down no more than 4 minutes later and the van has been moved and they were demanding me to pay for an hour of parking. Telling me I cant just leave the van parked there. Like are you guys fucking idiots? Did you clearly not see me running up and down to move things in? I wasn't just leaving the van there for fun and games. The stupid dude NEVER TOLD ME IF I STAYED THERE, THEY WILL CHARGE ME. HE JUST ASKED FOR THE KEYS AND GAVE ME SOME BULLSHIT EXCUSE. I argued my way out of it and was able to leave without paying. Literally the worst people. I literally fucking live there.

reviews.name: Sherri S.
reviews.review: ***DOG OWNERS BEWARE*** I began parking here on 9/3/2019 and on 9/16/2019-- after dropping my dog off at doggie day care-- I was told by the attendant that I was no longer able to park there because my car still smelled like my dog. It's a garage. A. Garage. full of mold, exhaust, and dust. I found parking down the street for the same price with less ridiculous valets. Also, their elevator was broken the entire time I parked there.

They just raised their Early Bird Special (9:30am - 7:30pm) to $20.

When I explained to the attendant that the sign on Mission Street said it was $18, he was rude and basically said its if you don't want to park here for $40, them turn around and leave. He was completely rude and had manners to us.

reviews.review: We had a terrible experience with this garage - we had a pre-paid, guaranteed reservation which they would not honor because they supposedly had to save the open spaces for a convention. Sounded like a scam to us. Will not be back.

reviews.name: Walter G.
reviews.review:
Parked car at 9am on a Saturday for a $45.00 fee for 24 hours. I picked it up at 10:15 the next day.  The rates are posted, however, when you check your car in they do not review them with you. Very quick to tell you $45 for 24 hours. Rasheed and Kamel blame the price gouging on their computer and will tell you it comes out of their pay if they adjust it. Not their fault I suppose. Owners rules.
I parked my car there from 8:30am on Saturday to 10:00am on sunday (25 1/2 hours and it cost me $77.50.
LET THE BUYER BEWARE.  All legal I guess but if you can park somewhere else you will avoid the shifty PRICE GOUGING here.
